  <discussion>Sclerocactus cloverae is characterized by its very dense spines and small (relative
        to S. parviflorus) purple flowers. Phylogenetic analyses of chloroplast DNA sequences
        support a close relationship among S. cloverae, S. whipplei, and S. parviflorus (J. M.
        Porter et al. 2000). Populations with all reproductive individuals maintaining juvenile
        morphology have been segregated as S. cloverae subsp. brackii K. D. Heil &amp; J. M.
        Porter.</discussion>
